description: Travellers from some English regions must self-isolate for 14 days from Tuesday, the States says.
title: Coronavirus: Guernsey to enforce 14-day quarantine for some UK arrivals
title_page: Coronavirus: Guernsey to enforce 14-day quarantine for some UK arrivals - BBC News
maintext: Director of Public Health Dr Nicola Brink warned islanders the regions were likely to move between Group B and A in the next few weeks "at very short notice" and they may need to self-isolate for longer than "originally anticipated".
